<h1>Problem 810 - 2014 ELMOSL, C5</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a positive integer. For any \(k\), denote by \(a_k\) the number of permutations of \(\{1,2,\dots,n\}\) with exactly \(k\) disjoint cycles. (For example, if \(n=3\) then \(a_2=3\) since \((1)(23)\), \((2)(31)\), \((3)(12)\) are the only such permutations.) Evaluate \[a_n n^n + a_{n-1} n^{n-1} + \dots + a_1 n.\]</p>
